<p>I have a <code>ViewPager</code> with current initizlization of an item :</p>  <pre><code> @Override     public Object instantiateItem(ViewGroup container, int position) {         final DateSelectorPageView v = new DateSelectorPageView(mContext, mListener);         container.addView(v, new LinearLayout.LayoutParams(LayoutParams.MATCH_PARENT, LayoutParams.WRAP_CONTENT));         return v;     } </code></pre>  <p>In <code>DateSelectorPageView</code> i have 4 views, which needs to be clicked, so by default i;m using <code>OnClickListener</code> :</p>  <pre><code>mView[i].setOnClickListener(this); </code></pre>  <p>With this realization i can click on current view and <code>click</code> will work, and swipe on area other from the view and it will swipe, but i need to botch swipe and click on this item. Already Tried:</p>  <pre><code>   @Override     public boolean onTouch(View v, MotionEvent e) {         if(e.getAction() == MotionEvent.ACTION_DOWN) {             x = e.getX();             return true;         }         if(e.getAction() == MotionEvent.ACTION_UP &amp;&amp; Math.abs(e.getX() - x) &lt; 30) {             onClick(v);         }         return false;     } </code></pre>  <p>The thing with <code>onTouch</code> is that when i'm returning <code>true</code> it will be called again but swipe will not work, but if i return <code>false</code> swipe will work, but other actions, such as <code>ACTION_UP</code> will no be called.</p>  <p><strong>Interesting thing:</strong> space which is empty from <code>TextViews</code> and <code>Buttons</code> is working fine, i guess it has something to do witch clickable views, and i've tried things like :</p>  <pre><code>android:descendantFocusability="blocksDescendants" </code></pre>  <p>and all things with <code>focusability</code> and <code>clickable</code>, also with <code>setHorizontalScrolling(false)</code></p>  <p><strong>IF SOMEONE WILL FACE IT:</strong> If you have <code>TextView</code> with <code>gravity</code> set to <code>center</code> and <code>singleLine</code> is set to <code>true</code> - it will not swipe, it's a appers to be a known problem</p>